text.p: These are some of the leading stories in the official Iraqi press on Saturday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.
- Iraq accuses Kuwait of undertaking "illegitimate actions" in its territorial waters
- Arab League warns against foreign interference in Iraq's domestic affairs
- Arab unionists call for the removal of sanctions on Iraq
- Iraq foils attempt to transfer headquarters of Arab engineers union from Baghdad to Cairo
- Iraqi Oil Transport Company's profits rise by 75 percent over last year
- Tunisian official calls for the lifting of sanctions on Iraq
- Riots erupt in Amman stadium following end of football match
- Moslems in Britain urged to boycott general elections
- Germany put off its response to Boutros-Ghali's nomination
- Health ministry engineers repair medical equipment
(The above were also carried by JUMHOURIYA and AL-IRAQ)
- Editorial accuses U.S. of attempts to dismember Iraq
